    "content": "[h2]Synopsis[/h2]\r\n\r\nA series of disturbances plagues the Grand Bazaar of Khetem, an endlessly changing maze of stalls filled with incredible wares, enticing smells, and magical lights.  Accusations fly as the characters become entangled in a feud between the well-respected Asrani and Jadari merchant families of Y'Matara. To prevent the families’ conflict from escalating, the characters must earn the trust of the market’s vendors and gain their help to unmask who’s behind a rash of vandalism and thefts.\r\n\r\n[h2]Adventure Hook[/h2]\r\nThe characters find a flyer inviting people to join the Night Markets at the @[Great Bazaar of Khetem](landmark:c912ecdd-44d7-4e87-a40f-21f258467441), an event that occurs every two weeks, where the Bazaar is opened at night (usually it is closed at night).\r\n\r\n[center][section:lore-box][img:6470321][/section][/center]\r\n\r\n[h2]Adventure Background[/h2]\r\n\r\nThe Asrani and Jadari families have always had a complicated relationship. While their trades and relationships to the @[Great Bazaar of Khetem](landmark:c912ecdd-44d7-4e87-a40f-21f258467441) differ, their stubbornness and intense family loyalty are the same. Both believe they’re paragons of what a market merchant should be while also believing the other family has been jealously sabotaging them for years. Despite this, the current heads of the two families,  @[Sahira Asrani](person:bf785367-4496-4868-8f1c-3cca9d094092)and @[Basim Jadari](person:041bb09c-0d99-4560-b80d-75fd539b0189), have vowed not to continue what is now a multigenerational rivalry. These family heads have even begun to seek each other’s counsel and plant the seeds of friendship. But in recent weeks, thefts and vandalism targeting both families’ businesses have rekindled old suspicions, and the feud threatens to reignite.",
